# AWS-0132: S3 bucket not encrypted with a customer managed key (CMK).
# The state bucket uses SSE-S3 (AES256), which is sufficient for a personal
# project. A KMS CMK would add cost and operational overhead without
# meaningful security benefit here.
AVD-AWS-0132

# AWS-0009: Instance has a public IP address.
# The jump box requires a public IP for outbound connectivity to SSM endpoints.
# The security group has no inbound rules, so the instance is unreachable from
# the internet.
AVD-AWS-0009

# AWS-0104: Security group allows unrestricted egress.
# Port 443 egress to 0.0.0.0/0 is required to reach AWS SSM endpoints, which
# are managed by AWS and have no fixed IP ranges to restrict to.
AVD-AWS-0104
